item.title: Bin Larden
item.dc:creator: @Frell Frell
item.description:
@Frell wrote:

Some don't consider throwing his body into the ocean to be a proper burial Some don't consider killing him to be lawful Some don't consider it justice Some don't consider it right to cross borders to kill him Some think we owe an apology to the muslim world

I don’t consider disintegration by metal on metal collisions, jumping to death, burning to death, or being crushed to death a proper burial
I don’t consider killing 3000 lawful
I consider it justice revenge, as a big fuck you to Al Qaeda
I don’t consider crossing borders for 9/11 right
When they killed 3000 we didn’t demand an apology, but because we kill one, they want one?

The main point is we’ve rolled over the war by killing an important figure in the enemies world. Instead of nit picking Iraq for 10 years and our presence causing about a million Iraqi casualties, I would have preferred special forces from the start. We wouldn’t have been dressing up for the enemy, while they are hidden from us, we wouldn’t have had so many wounded and killed from IED’s if they knew we weren’t driving around there, and they would have been oblivious to us had we not bitten off more than we could chew.
